"organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2017-03-15T20:23:00Z","updated_at":"2017-03-15T20:23:00Z","body":"Mind you, I currently use this, which is simple but does the trick:\r\n```rust\r\nuse rocket::request::{self, Request, FromRequest};\r\nuse rocket::response::{Flash};\r\nuse rocket::Outcome::{Success, Failure};\r\nuse rocket::http::Status;\r\n\r\n#[derive(Debug, Serialize)]\r\npub struct FlashMessage {\r\n    pub name: String,\r\n    pub message: String,\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl From<Flash<()>> for FlashMessage {\r\n    fn from(flash: Flash<()>) -> Self {\r\n        FlashMessage {name: flash.name().into(), message: flash.msg().into()}\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nimpl<'a, 'r> FromRequest<'a, 'r> for FlashMessage {\r\n    type Error = ();\r\n\r\n    fn from_request(request: &'a Request<'r>) -> request::Outcome<Self, Self::Error> {\r\n        if let Success(flash) = Flash::from_request(request) {\r\n            Success(flash.into())\r\n        }\r\n        else {\r\n            Failure((Status::NotFound, ()))\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rwf2/Rocket/issues/comments/286867095/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"lholden","id":20953,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIwOTUz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/20953?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden","html_url":"https://github.com/lholden","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lholden/following{/other_use